snippet.textDisplay: The Aussies' middle order needs tinkering. The batting is probably one power batsman short eg. Maxwell, Stoinis or M Marsh. Turner has been out of form. snippet.textDisplay:
it’s pre obvious aus are missing maxwell and stoinis. i’ve got the perfect solution: maxwell in place of turner and stoinis in place of agar. here’s why
smith and labuschagne act as innings builders or “anchors” who are fine with putting away the bad balls and are masterful at finding 1s and 2s. the problem here is these two can’t bat together as it forces one of them to play out of their comfort zone early which is not what their role is. instead i think that obviously warner and finch should open, and if a wicket should fall, smith comes in as the one to repair and rebuild the innings. but then from here if one of warner or finch get out, stoinis should come in to partner smith, acting as an explosive player. from here there are many options. if smith would get out early, labuschagne goes in, and if stoinis gets out early, carey goes in. maxwell should always be brought in as a last 10-15 over effort, as his role is the x factor of the team. he will go in and score maybe a 70 off 35 balls, which is just his role. the reason agar is not here is because australia are needing an explosive batsman more than a controlling left arm spinner. with the presence of labuschagne and smith, stoinis and maxwells presence are almost compulsory. and the added bonus is that both are allrounders, giving more depth to the already stacked bowling lineup, which is starc, cummins, hazelwood and zampa.
